COMERIO ERCOLE S.p.A.
Established in 1885, COMERIO ERCOLE S.p.A. is an internationally recognized manufacturer of machines and complete industrial plants for the rubber and plastic processing industries, with a strong specialization in calendering and mixing technologies.
Headquartered in Busto Arsizio/Castellanza (Italy), the company operates over 40,000 sqm of main production area plus 15,000 sqm of additional nearby facilities. With a team of over 250 skilled professionals, COMERIO ERCOLE integrates all operations internally — from design and engineering to manufacturing, installation, training, and after-sales service.
 Core Competencies & Divisions
Rubber Division
·        Patented two-roll mixing mills: mobobloc, unidrive, semi-unidrive, pluridrive (up to 3050 mm)
·        Internal mixers up to 370 liters, batch-off cooling plants, crackers and refiners
·        2-3-4 roll calenders and roller-head solutions
·        Complete lines for fabric frictioning, textile/steel cord coating, and rubber sheeting
·        Automatic wind-up systems, vulcanizing rotary machines, hydraulic presses
·        Full turnkey production systems for tires and conveyor belts
·        Recovery systems for rubber scrap from end-of-life tires
Plastic Division
·        Horizontal, vertical, F and L-type calenders with 2 to 5 rolls
·        Suitable for PVC, TPO, PP film and sheets
·        Full lines for dosing, mixing, and calendering soft, semi-rigid, and rigid plastics
·        Modernization and revamping services for existing calendering plants
 R&D and Innovation
COMERIO ERCOLE is certified to ISO 9001:2015, ISO 14001:2015, and ISO 45001:2018, and is firmly committed to sustainability, ESG standards, and social responsibility.
·        Over 3.0% of annual turnover is invested in R&D (2024: €1.9 million)
·        In the past five years, 8 new patents were developed, primarily for the tire industry
·        Two dedicated laboratories and a 350 sqm R&D center support customer co-development projects
·        Acts as an authorized laboratory for technological research with international collaborations
Since 2023, the company has also launched a specialized Industry 5.0 division focused on IoT technologies, remote maintenance (teleservice) and digital diagnostics, enabling predictive and sustainable plant operation worldwide.
 Training & Services
Through the Athena® Academy, COMERIO ERCOLE delivers specialized training programs to customers and internal personnel, promoting a long-standing "Culture of Quality" within its organization.
A fully structured Customer Service Department manages:
·        Remote support and commissioning
·        Technical documentation and compliance
·        Spare parts logistics and revamping
·        Preventive maintenance and troubleshooting
