EMS-CHEMIE (Deutschland) Vertriebs GmbH
EMS-GRIVORY at a glance

EMS-GRIVORY is part of the Business Unit High Performance Polymers of the EMS Group and employs more than 800 people worldwide. The largest development and production center is located in Domat/Ems, Switzerland. Other production sites are located in Germany, China, Taiwan and the USA. In addition, we have development and sales organizations in all major markets in Europe, Asia and the Americas, enabling us to reach our customers quickly on site.

We act customer-oriented, worldwide and fast
The specific needs of the markets are met by the independent but closely cooperating business units EMS-GRIVORY Europe, EMS-GRIVORY Asia and EMS-GRIVORY America. Customers benefit from a locally competent and globally close cooperation of these business units in marketing & sales, research & development, application engineering and production.

EMS-GRIVORY - The leading specialist for high-performance polyamides
Polyamides are among the most versatile and high-performance plastics of all. EMS-GRIVORY is the supplier worldwide with the widest range of polyamide materials. These high-performance plastics for injection molding and extrusion processing are offered worldwide under the brand names Grivory®, Grilamid® and Grilon®. Polyamides from EMS-GRIVORY are used in the market segments automotive, industrial & consumer goods, electrical & electronics, telecommunications, optics, medical technology and packaging.

We always find a solution!
EMS-GRIVORY''s strengths lie not only in the development and manufacture of these high-performance plastics, but also in the development of innovative system solutions with customers around the world. The focus is on reducing costs and weight by replacing metals; however, EMS-GRIVORY also offers unique solutions for demanding surfaces, designs and colors.

To this end, EMS-GRIVORY provides intensive support to customers throughout the entire development process and also beyond during ongoing series production. The services are individually tailored to the customer''s needs in the respective market segment. Starting with initial feasibility studies and profitability analyses, experienced development engineers accompany customers during prototype production, specific component testing and optimization of tools and process technology. If necessary, products are adapted to specific requirements. This provides our customers with a complete solution and enables them to differentiate themselves in their market through cost savings, weight reduction or new designs.
