Terbrack Kunststoff GmbH & Co. KG
Future-oriented from the very beginning.

For more than 60 years TERBRACK has been known as a pioneer in the production and processing of high-quality engineering plastics.

Already at its foundation in 1954 TERBRACK started innovatively and was the first company to process so-called ultra-high molecular weight and high molecular weight polyethylenes. Customers all over the world benefit from these products from Vreden in Münsterland, which are initially manufactured as pressed sheets at TERBRACK and then further processed into finished parts that can be found in almost the entire machinery and plant engineering sector.

Extruded profiles and round bars as chain and belt guides, guide rails and sliding strips complement or extend the manufacturing and thus the application possibilities.

In particular, ultrahigh-molecular-weight polyethylenes, which are, incidentally, an extraordinarily special material among plastics, represent a significant advantage due to their outstanding sliding properties, low mechanical wear, the extremely high impact strength as well as the good chemical resistance, they can be used in a wide range of applications as lining elements in silo and bunker linings, ships and trucks, in filling and packaging plants, in transport, storage and conveyor technology, in chemical and electroplating technology as seals, sliding and guide rollers, gear wheels for fittings as well as in the food industry, etc. are also used.

Reliable quality, selected raw materials as well as strict and permanent controls during the entire process chain guarantee the quality of our products
In addition, our qualities comply with the valid food regulations. (EU 10/2011/EG; FDA: 21 CFR 177.1520; FDA: 21 CFR 178.3297)
Computer-controlled manufacturing processes ensure a consistently high level of semi-finished and finished parts.

Many years ago TERBRACK introduced a quality management system according to the international standard DIN EN ISO 9001:2015, as well as an energy management system according to ISO 50001.

TERBRACK is today with about 120 employees one of the leading producers in the field of processing ultra-high and high molecular weight polyethylenes. But also other high performance polymers are processed at TERBRACK.
For this purpose, we have state-of-the-art facilities at our disposal on a covered production and storage area of 16,000 sqm at one location.

Based on our decades of experience and a consistent orientation towards the future, we realize individual technical solutions together with our customers
