Frilvam S.p.a.
A company that’s international in scope, but with the heart and customer service of a family-run operation. That’s Frilvam, with 70 years of experience in the coloration and additivization of thermoplastic polymers and, today, an Italian leader in the production of Masterbatches in black, white, in color or with special-effects, and biodegradables, as well as a wide range of additive Masterbatches to meet all the most specific needs.
  
Founded in the first years after World War II, Frilvam, based in northern Italy in Milan, began by marketing neutral and colored thermoplastic resins made by other manufacturers, but soon set up its own plants for the production of sample color products.

The customer service and continuous research and development that characterized its business right from the start quickly turned Frilvam into an important player in the field of technopolymers and charged and colored compounds. With the experience and know-how accumulated over the years, it eventually presented its own line of Masterbatches for thermoplastic resins.

Today, Frilvam is a leader in the Masterbatch sector; technologically advanced, it stands out for a significant flexibility of production which makes it capable of satisfying clients’ every need in the most wide-ranging sectors of application. With its own internal Chemical Lab, its relentless R&D work, and a territorial diversification with the opening of plants in Modena and France, Frilvam founds its business on listening and understanding the needs of its customers, who are always viewed as partners with whom to decide on the most suitable formulations for every specific need.

Our extensive experience, moreover, also allows us to offer our customers support from a normative and legislative standpoint, a service which is customized according to the country in question.

The UNI-EN ISO 9001:2015 certification, belonging to the Nerviano headquarter (soon also available in the other locations), guarantees Frilvam’s quality and the reliability of its products.
But most of all it is customer satisfaction that makes our company proud of its 70 years of activity. An international outlook, but with the heart of a family that’s always committed, every day, to doing the right thing.

The important Plast 2018 fair in Milan provided the perfect occasion to celebrate the company’s 70th anniversary in the best possible way. This is where Frilvam decided to celebrate such a prestigious milestone together with its many customers, publicly unveiling the new logo and launching its  renewed range of products and a catalogue with totally revised graphics and layout.
 
The goal of yesterday, today and tomorrow is to be our customers’ essential partner for the realization of their creative/productive process.

By guaranteeing customers the widest range of products on the market, the highest standards of quality, pre-and post-sale technical assistance, and fast, on-time service, we put ourselves forward not as simple supplier but as a solid partner, a reliable, expert leader in the masterbatch sector.
