FARREL POMINI® is a global leader in the design and manufacture of compounding systems for a wide range of processing applications.

Since introducing the Farrel Continuous Mixer (FCM™) in 1963 and later the CP Series II™ Compact Processor, FARREL POMINI has delivered proven technologies with production capacities from 30 kg/h to 40,000 kg/h. Key applications include rigid and flexible PVC, flooring compounds, flame retardants, biodegradable plastics, recycled materials, highly filled compounds, white and black masterbatch, and petrochemical finishing. Recent innovations include solutions that eliminate costly secondary equipment in rigid PVC processing and a direct-to-deck board process that removes the pellet milling step.

FARREL POMINI® offers robust mechanical recycling solutions, designed to handle diverse feedstocks with irregular sizes, shapes, low bulk density, moisture, volatiles, and contaminants. In chemical recycling, the FCM™ is integral to pyrolysis systems, including WF RECYCLE-TECH’s patented tire recycling process and Lummus Technology’s PE & PP flexible film recycling system.

Beyond equipment, FARREL POMINI® provides comprehensive aftermarket and consulting services, including spare parts, start-up and commissioning, equipment lifecycle support, remanufacturing, and repair. Our Project Engineering Team supports plant design, integration, and full-line solutions.

At our Customer Demonstration Facilities in Ansonia, Connecticut (USA) and Rochdale, UK, customers can run production- or lab-scale trials to optimize formulations, compare equipment, and evaluate processing parameters. These trials provide guaranteed production data, process expertise, and confidence in capital investment decisions.

For more information, visit www.farrel-pomini.com or call +1 203 736 5500.
